â–¶ ğ“ğšğ¢ğ§ğ­: A taint is a property applied to a node in a Kubernetes cluster that indicates a special condition or preference about the types of pods that can be scheduled onto that node. Taints are typically used to repel certain pods from being scheduled on specific nodes, thereby influencing the scheduling decisions made by the Kubernetes scheduler.

