â–¶ ğ“ğ¨ğ¥ğğ«ğšğ­ğ¢ğ¨ğ§: Toleration, on the other hand, is a property specified within a pod's configuration that indicates the pod's ability to tolerate specific taints on nodes. When a pod has tolerations set, it can be scheduled in nodes with corresponding taints that match the tolerations. Toleration allows you to control which nodes a pod can be scheduled on, even if those nodes have certain taints applied.
